    var aFlag = true;
    loadLayers.intoStack(fList, aFlag);
}
runLoadStack(folder)
```

I immediately noticed the `@include` method of importing the stack methods, I can not find any official documentation for this (also not friendly with minification). Also, if the script is not placed with the same directory as `Load Files into Stack.jsx` it will throw the error `Unable to open file: anonymous`. And even after solving all of these issues when I run the .jsx script from within my extension using `$.evalFile()` I am having the same error as if the script is not in the correct directory: `Unable to open file: anonymous`. [Error is being thrown on line 762 of an imported jsx](https://github.com/LeZuse/photoshop-scripts/blob/master/default/Stack%20Scripts%20Only/CreateImageStack.jsx#L762).

Any help resolving the error I am experiencing or simply on how to load an array of image paths into layers (faster method) will be greatly appreciated!

